---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import './Legal.css';
---
<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | Trilogy Training"
  description="Terms and conditions for using the Trilogy Training website and coaching services."
  canonicalPath="/terms/"
  ogTitle="Terms of Service | Trilogy Training"
  ogDescription="Terms and conditions for using the Trilogy Training website and coaching services."
>
  <Section background="default" class="section--page-header">
    <div class="legal-hero">
      <p class="legal-hero__label">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="legal-hero__title">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-hero__subtitle">
        The terms and conditions governing your use of our website and coaching services.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section background="alt">
    <div class="legal-content">
      <p class="legal-content__updated">Last updated: 24 March 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Overview</h2>
      <p>
        These terms govern your use of the Trilogy Training website (www.trilogy-training.com) and any coaching services provided by Trilogy Training. By using our website or engaging our services, you agree to these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Coaching Services</h2>

      <h3>Nature of services</h3>
      <p>
        Trilogy Training provides personalised endurance coaching programmes for triathletes, runners, swimmers, and cyclists. Our coaching includes training plan design, ongoing plan adjustments, and communication with your assigned coach.
      </p>

      <h3>Free consultation</h3>
      <p>
        We offer a free initial consultation to discuss your goals and determine if our coaching is a good fit. This consultation does not commit you to any paid services.
      </p>

      <h3>Not medical advice</h3>
      <p>
        Our coaching services are not a substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. You should consult a qualified healthcare provider before starting any new exercise programme. By engaging our coaching services, you confirm that you are in suitable health to participate in endurance training.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Assumption of Risk</h2>
      <p>
        Endurance sports carry inherent risks including but not limited to physical injury, illness, and fatigue. By using our coaching services, you acknowledge and accept these risks. You are responsible for training within your own limits and listening to your body.
      </p>
      <p>
        Trilogy Training and its coaches shall not be held liable for any injury, illness, or damage arising from following our training plans or coaching advice, except in cases of gross negligence.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Payment and Subscriptions</h2>
      <p>
        Coaching plans are offered on a monthly subscription basis as outlined on our <a href="/plans/">Plans &amp; Pricing</a> page. Details of pricing, billing cycles, and what is included in each plan are specified at the time of sign-up.
      </p>

      <h3>Cancellation</h3>
      <p>
        You may cancel your coaching subscription at any time by notifying your coach or contacting us at <a href="mailto:adam.labbett@gmail.com">adam.labbett@gmail.com</a>. Cancellations take effect at the end of the current billing period. We do not offer refunds for partial months.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Your Responsibilities</h2>
      <p>As a client, you agree to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide accurate information about your health, fitness, and training history</li>
        <li>Communicate openly with your coach about how training is going</li>
        <li>Inform us of any injuries, illnesses, or changes in your health</li>
        <li>Train safely and within your capabilities</li>
        <li>Seek medical attention when needed</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on this website, including text, images, design, and branding, is the property of Trilogy Training and is protected by copyright. Training plans provided to you are for your personal use only and may not be shared, redistributed, or resold.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Website Use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to use this website lawfully and not to engage in any activity that could damage, disable, or impair the site. We reserve the right to restrict access to any user who violates these terms.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, Trilogy Training's total liability to you for any claim arising from our services shall not exceed the amount you have paid us in the three months preceding the claim. We are not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Your use of our website and services is also governed by our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>, which describes how we collect and use your personal data.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by Swiss law. Any disputes shall be resolved in the courts of Switzerland, unless otherwise required by applicable consumer protection laws in your country of residence.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date. Continued use of our website or services after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about these terms, contact us at <a href="mailto:adam.labbett@gmail.com">adam.labbett@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</Layout>
